moking Service, you are four times more likely to quit than using willpower alone.”The road show will be visiting Tesco in Newcastle Road, Simonside, South Shields, today, tomorrow, January 27 and 28, and February 2 to 4. It will also be at Asda in Coronation Street, South Shields, tomorrow and Saturday, as well as January 27 and 28 and February 17 and 18.Email to a friendPrint this pageLogged in as:Comment here.Please adhere to our Community guidelinesYour viewPlease sign in to be able to comment on this story.Top storiesFitness expert Kate’s here to work it out!Alert after rise in whooping cough casesTwo-day booze break ‘a start’ says campaignerPanto star tells slimmers ‘Oh yes you can lose weight!’Back to health after festive excessesNewsLocal NewsRegional NewsNational NewsBusinessCrimeEducationPoliticsHealthTraffic & TravelCampaignsHealthBehind the headlinesPopularMost commentsMost sharedTransfer rumours: Sunday, January 8Middlesbrough star sorry for Sunderland insultInjury worry for Newcastle as reserves beat WiganTransfer Rumours update: Thursday, January 12Friendly rival’s sadness at death of ‘Podgy’Oxbridge places inequality ‘disgrace’Ponies to beat the credit munchAtom bomb veterans set for new fightPolice probe house party deathMurder probe launched after Hebburn house party‘Stop attack on public sector’ - leaderSearch for:
